    "E.W. Bullinger": "). It is 2 Thess. i. 6-8 that we have here. When the time has come for Him to\n\"gather out of His kingdom all things that offend\" (Matt. xiii. 41), \"immediately He putteth\nin the sickle, because the harvest is come\" (Mark iv. 29). Matt. xxiv. 37-42 must be read in\nconnection with the scene here referred to. The good may be gathered into barns: these\nbarns are seen in the next chapter; but the though connected with the harvest is judgment.\nAnd why a \"sharp\" sickle. The vintage is admittedly judicial (\nverses 18-20), and that is\ngathered with a sharp sickle. That the harvest is judicial also is confirmed by a reference to\nJer. li. 33: \"Thus saith the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel; The daughter of Babylon is like"
